    {
      "id": "1481881721036210277",
      "type": "Default",
      "timestamp": "2026-03-13T05:08:54.326+00:00",
      "timestampEdited": null,
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "Well, it is system verilog, I could share the testbench structure. Basically, I had students design everything from the 8b10b output to the 10b8b input via schematics in FreePDK15 and FreePDK3. I could help stand up the FreePDKs at least from questions and simulations if needed. I upgraded the FreePDK15 to have integration in cadence instead of python wrappers and I did the TCAD to Spice on the models and setup a cadence PDK for schematics (no DRC/LVS).",
      "author": {
        "id": "1034663307598123049",
        "name": "wspitts2",
        "discriminator": "0000",
        "nickname": "beardothaweirdo",
        "color": null,
        "isBot": false,
